quran[22]{c,v,t}:
  38,62,"And they say, “What is the matter with us that we do not see the men whom we thought were evil?”"
  38,63,"“Did we mock at them or did our eyes turn away from them?”"
  38,64,"Indeed this is really true – the people of the hell quarrelling among themselves."
  38,65,"Proclaim (O dear Prophet Mohammed – peace and blessings be upon him), “I am purely a Herald of Warning – and there is no God except Allah, the One, the All Dominant.”"
  38,66,"“Lord of the heavens and the earth and all that is between them – the Almighty, the Oft Forgiving.”"
  38,67,"Say, “That is a great tidings.”"
  38,68,"“You are neglectful of it!”"
  38,69,"“What did I know of the heavenly world, when the angels had disputed.”"
  38,70,"“I receive only the divine revelations, that I am purely a clear Herald of Warning.”"
  38,71,"(Remember) When your Lord said to the angels, “I will create a human from clay.” –"
  38,72,"“So when I have perfected him and breathed into him a spirit from Myself, (you all) fall down before him in prostration.”"
  38,73,"So all the angels prostrated, every one, without exception."
  38,74,"Except Iblis; he was proud and was, from the beginning, a disbeliever."
  38,75,"Said Allah, “O Iblis! What prevented you from prostrating before one whom I have created with My hands*? Have you become proud or were you haughty from the beginning?” (Used as a metaphor)."
  38,76,"Said Iblis, “I am better than him; You made me from fire, and You have created him from clay!”"
  38,77,"He said, “Therefore exit from heaven, for you have been outcast.” (To disrespect the Prophets – peace and blessings be upon them – is blasphemy.)"
  38,78,"“And indeed My curse is upon you till the Day of Judgement.”"
  38,79,"He said, “My Lord! Therefore give me respite till the day when all will be raised.”"
  38,80,"Said Allah, “You are therefore among those given respite.”"
  38,81,"“Until the time of the known day.”"
  38,82,"He said, “Therefore, by oath of Your honour, I will surely mislead all of them.”"
  38,83,"“Except Your chosen bondmen among them.”"
